text.section:
The board of trustees shall:
Maintain responsibility for all moneys collected or disbursed from the group;
Maintain minutes of its meetings and make the minutes available to the commissioner;
Designate an administrator to carry out the policies established by the board of trustees and to provide day-to-day management of the group, and delineate in the written minutes of its meetings the areas of authority it delegates to the administrator; and
Establish a formal conflict-of-interest policy or code of conduct applicable to the board of trustees, officers, and employees that includes a description of the system used to monitor compliance with the conflict-of-interest policy or code of conduct.
